snippet.textDisplay:
It is always amusing to see how people watch a show whose real premise was always experimentation, and then have a problem with month songs in which any experimentation is done. 
Especially so this season. Kinda reminds me of the response to that last Rohail Hayat season - when people could not comprehend that the logical next stage for the show was to go truly international. 
Such vitriol one sees in the comments simply because people bring their own prejudice to a show which is all about open ended and honest attempt at pushing the boundaries further and farther...

People are ignoring the message of hope and good times ahead in the song, its not that subliminal and vague. Kind of idealistic, utopian, but hopeful thinking about the future, they can make it happen, no need to despair kind of message. 

Also the message is clear 'don't regret the past' and look forward to life and take it on the strides... as Momina has said 'the inspiration for her is she herself' and this shows the need for confidence and self esteem in whatever a person do. 

Get the message and not just the face value of it young folks, to whom the song is meant for.
